Create pretty kable tables with custom bolding options.

prettyKable.Rd

Make pretty kable tables and enable easy bolding of cells in kable (across rows, columns, or the entire table).

prettyKable(
  X,
  digits = 3,
  sigfig = T,
  align = "c",
  caption = "",
  format = c("html", "latex"),
  na_disp = "NA",
  bold_function = NULL,
  bold_margin = NULL,
  bold_scheme = T,
  bold_color = NULL,
  full_width = NULL,
  position = "center",
  font_size = NULL,
  fixed_thead = F,
  scroll = F,
  scroll_width = NULL,
  scroll_height = NULL,
  return_df = FALSE,
  ...
)

Arguments

X

Data frame or data matrix to display in table
digits

Number of digits to display for numeric values
sigfig

Logical. If TRUE, digits refers to the number of significant figures. If FALSE, digits refers to the number of decimal places.
align

A character vector indicating the column alignment, e.g., 'c'. For further details, see knitr::kable().
caption

The table caption.
format

One of "html" or "latex", indicating the output format.
na_disp

Character string to display if NA entry is found in table.
bold_function

Optional function string or vector of function strings to use for bolding entries, e.g. ". == max(.)" or ". >= 0.5".
bold_margin

Specifies the margins of X that will be used to evaluate bold_function across, i.e., 0 = across entire matrix, 1 = across rows, and 2 = across columns. Required if bold_function = TRUE.
bold_scheme

Scalar or vector of logicals, indicating whether or not to apply bold_function to row if bold_margin = 1 and to column if bold_margin = 1, 2. Default is to apply bolding to all rows/columns.
bold_color

Color of bolded text.
full_width

Logical. Whether or not table should have full width. See kableExtra::kable_styling() for details.
position

Character string determining how to position table on page; possible values inclue "left", "right", "center", "float_left", "float_right". See kableExtra::kable_styling() for details.
font_size

A numeric input for table font size. See kableExtra::kable_styling() for details.
fixed_thead

Logical. Whether or not table header should be fixed at top. See kableExtra::kable_styling() for details.
scroll

Logical. If TRUE, add scroll box. Only used if format = "html".
scroll_width

A character string indicating width of the scroll box, e.g., "50px", "100%". See kableExtra::scroll_box() for details.
scroll_height

A character string indicating height of the scroll box, e.g. "100px". See kableExtra::scroll_box() for details.
return_df

Logical. If TRUE, return data frame that was used as input into knitr::kable() in addition to the kable output. If FALSE, only return the kable output.
...

Additional arguments to pass to knitr::kable().

Value

If return_df = FALSE, returns a kable object. Otherwise, returns a list of two:

kable

A kable object.

df

A data frame that was used as input into knitr::kable().

Examples

## Show iris data table
prettyKable(iris, align = "c", caption = "Iris Data Table")
